==文化==

[[聖經|聖經]]中有所謂的“[[芥菜種的比喻|芥菜種的比喻]]”<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Mark%204&version=NIV |title=Mark 4 - The Parable of the Sower |website=The Parable of the Sower |publisher=New International Version of the Bible |accessdate=9 June 2016 |archive-date=2021-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416221357/http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=mark%204&version=NIV |dead-url=no }}</ref>，英語世界中它曾被稱爲“eye of newt”（[[肋突螈亚科|蠑螈]]眼睛），因此常與[[莎士比亞|莎士比亞]]的《[[麥克白|麥克白]]》中巫術所用的真蠑螈眼睛相混淆<ref>{{cite web |url=http://people.howstuffworks.com/is-eye-of-newt-real-thing.htm |title=Is eye of newt a real thing? |author=Debra Ronca |deadurl=no |accessdate=12 August 2016 |archive-date=2020-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201214546/https://people.howstuffworks.com/is-eye-of-newt-real-thing.htm }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buzzle.com/articles/meaning-of-shakespeares-macbeth-quote-eye-of-newt-and-toe-of-frog.html |title=Meaning of Shakespeare's Macbeth Quote 'Eye of Newt, and Toe of Frog' |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2016-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815032455/http://www.buzzle.com/articles/meaning-of-shakespeares-macbeth-quote-eye-of-newt-and-toe-of-frog.html |archive-date=2016-08-15 }}</ref>。

芥菜籽在[[佛教|佛教]]中也有出現，由一名婦人請求[[释迦牟尼|释迦牟尼]]救回她死去的兒子，释迦牟尼便要她從一戶從未失去過親友的家庭裏帶來一把芥菜籽，之後婦人發現世上並無這樣的人家，由此意識到自己的自私<ref>{{cite web |author1=Sharman, Shreshtha |author2=Neeta Sharma |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vCCxP388oygC&pg=PA223&lpg=PA223 |title=Together with English Language & Literature (Term II) |page=222 |deadurl=no |accessdate=12 August 2016 |archive-date=2019-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722191730/https://books.google.com/books?id=vCCxP388oygC&pg=PA223&lpg=PA223 }}</ref><ref>Buddhaghosa - [https://books.google.com/books?id=16GJdvuhhLMC&q=Kisa+Gotami Buddhist legends, Volume 28 (published 1921)] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=16GJdvuhhLMC&q=Kisa+Gotami |date=20190721232243 }}</ref>。

[[猶太教|猶太教]]將人類已知的世界比作芥菜籽，以喻其小<ref>{{cite web |first=Jay |last=Michaelson |url=http://learnkabbalah.com/the_meaning_of_god/ |title=The meaning of God |publisher=Learnkabbalah.com |access-date=2016-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223021958/http://www.learnkabbalah.com/the_meaning_of_god/ |archive-date=2016-12-23 |dead-url=yes }} also ''[[WP:V|verification]]'' at [http://learnkabbalah.com/about_jay_michaelson/ about jay michaelson] {{Wayback|url=http://learnkabbalah.com/about_jay_michaelson/ |date=20161029151452 }}</ref>。猶太哲學家[[納賀蒙尼德|納賀蒙尼德]]則將宇宙之初比作芥菜籽<ref>{{cite web |author=Dr. Gerald Schroeder |url=http://www.aish.com/ci/sam/48951136.html |publisher=© 2011 Aish.com |title=Your Life, Your Judaism |access-date=2016-11-16 |archive-date=2021-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416020604/https://www.aish.com/ci/sam/48951136.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

